  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What should I do if I lost my Chase debit card?",
  "response": "If you've lost your Chase debit card, it's important to take immediate action to protect your account and minimize potential damage. Here's what you should do:\n\n1. **Contact Chase Immediately:**\n   - Call Chase customer service at 1-800-935-9935. They are available 24/7.\n   - Report the lost card and request to have it deactivated to prevent unauthorized use.\n\n2. **Check Your Account:**\n   - After deactivating your card, review your recent transactions to ensure there are no unauthorized charges.\n   - If you spot any suspicious activity, report it to Chase right away.\n\n3. **Request a Replacement Card:**\n   - When you call Chase, ask for a replacement debit card. They will usually send it to you within 3-5 business days.\n   - In the meantime, you can often use your account number for transactions or request a temporary card if available.\n\n4. **Update Automatic Payments:**\n   - If you have any automatic payments or subscriptions linked to your lost card, update them with your new card details once you receive your replacement.\n\n5. **Consider Additional Security Measures:**\n   - Change your online banking password and PIN as a precautionary measure.\n   - Enable two-factor authentication if you haven\u2019t already.\n\n6. **Monitor Your Account:**\n   - Keep a close eye on your account for the next few weeks to ensure no fraudulent activity occurs.\n\nBy following these steps, you can minimize the risks associated with losing your debit card and get back to using your account securely as soon as possible.",
